# Module Conventions

## ESM

This project uses ECMAScript Modules (`"type": "module"`). `verbatimModuleSyntax` is enabled.

- All relative imports MUST use `.js` extensions.
- Type-only imports MUST use `import type`.

```typescript
// ❌ Missing .js extension
import { TopicKey } from "../../types";
// ✅ Correct
import { TopicKey } from "../../types.js";
// ❌ Non-type import used only as a type

// ✅ Correct
import { SystemConfig, type SystemConfig } from "./index.js";
```

## Enums Over String Literals

All classified values use their enum. Never use raw strings where an enum exists.
